subject: Re: Fwd: Dear Beneficiary,
body:
Dear Dena,

IBAN is an International Bank Account Number which you can use when making
or receiving international payments. It's an additional number to help
overseas banks identify your account for payments, while Routing number
is a nine-digit code used to identify a financial institution in the United
States. Banks use routing numbers to direct the exchange of funds to and
from one another


Mr. Denise
